								<dl>
									<dt>Download:</dt>
<dd>
                                                                                <i class="icon-download-alt" style="vertical-align: midle;"></i>
                                                                                <span class="label label-info">Lift 2.5-M1:</span>
                                                                                <a href="https://github.com/lift/lift_25_sbt/tarball/master">TAR</a>
                                                                                or
                                                                                <a href="https://github.com/lift/lift_25_sbt/zipball/master">Zip</a>
                                                                                .
                                                                                <br />
                                                                                Expand the project, cd into the directory and then into
                                                                                "scala_29/lift_basic" subdirectory.
                                                                                Then type
                                                                                <pre class="prettyprint lang-scala">
 ./sbt
>   container:start
                                        </pre>
                                                                                and you should be able to browse to
                                                                                <code>http://localhost:8080</code>
                                                                                and see your running
                                                                                Lift app.
                                                                                <hr />
                                                                        </dd>



									<dd>
